                    <i class="fa fa-star" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-users" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <div>ratings are used to:</div>
                    <div>
                      <ul>
                        <li>match members to events</li>
                        <li>match members to other memebrs</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </p>

            <p>
              <b>Industry</b><br/>
              <span>
                <span>According to</span>
                <span><i>to Dirk Pfl itsch |</i></span>
                <span><%= link_to "http://www.leadingdatingsites.co.uk/uploads/onlinedating-market-uk-2015.pdf", "http://www.leadingdatingsites.co.uk/uploads/onlinedating-market-uk-2015.pdf", target:"_blank" %></span><br/>
                <span>
                  <ul>
                    <li>The industry is currently at £158.7 million for 2013</li>
                    <li>Mintel 2015 predicts the UK online-dating market will grow from £165m to £225m by 2019</li>
                    <li>Spefz falls in the dating service category of: Social-dating & Match-Making </li>
                    <li>Industry Trends 2014/2015: Market share (users): Social-Dating: 27.4% /Match-Making: 13.4% / Online-Personal-Dating: 19.1% / Adult-Dating: 27.4% / Niche Dating: 10.8%</li>
                    <li>Industry Trends 2014/2015: Market share (revenues): Social-Dating: 10.8% / Match-Making: 23.9% / Online-Personal-Dating: 27.9%  / Adult-Dating: 29.5% / Niche Dating: 7.9%</li>
                  </ul>
                </span>
              </span>
            </p><br/>

            <p>
              <b>Summary</b><br/>
              <span>We believe that our online events dating platform service could do amazingly well. We believe our inbuilt rating algorithm will attract users to attend our events – which most of our competitors do not have – Most of our competitors focus more on gathering random singles who are willing to pay to attend an event. We want to gather and group singles of similar interest, so the potential of members connecting will be much higher. We believe our users are likely to attend our events as we auto-match individuals to specific events (via our internal rating algorithm system based on personality, physical appearance and interests) in order to ensure they are able to network effectively and meet like-minded people of their calibre.</span><br/><br/>
            </p>

